lead_paragraph: Canada won the first rugby medal awarded at the Olympics for 92 years with a 33-10 victory over Britain in the inaugural women's sevens bronze medal match at the Rio de Janeiro Games on Monday.

headline.print_headline: First Rugby Medal in 92 Years Goes to Canada With Women's Bronze
